-- Southern Hemisphere Rugby Signs $437 Million, Five-Year Broadcasting Pact
-- Dan Baynes
-- 2010-04-21T23:21:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-21/southern-hemisphere-rugby-signs-437-million-five-year-broadcasting-pact.html

          
          
             The southern hemisphere rugby
alliance sold broadcasting rights to Tri-Nations and Super Rugby
matches over the next five years for $437 million.    
 The deal represents an increase of $114 million on the
equivalent contracts in the previous arrangements, the South
African Rugby Union said in an e-mailed statement.     
          
          


  


        